					";s:11:"author_name";s:11:"Tim Sheehan";s:10:"author_uri";s:29:"http://killerinfographics.com";s:5:"title";s:34:"Quick Content That Makes An Impact";s:4:"link";s:74:"http://killerinfographics.com/blog/quick-content-that-makes-an-impact.html";s:2:"id";s:38:"http://killerinfographics.com/?p=14269";s:7:"updated";s:20:"2018-02-07T00:44:20Z";s:9:"published";s:20:"2017-12-13T19:18:17Z";s:7:"summary";s:253:"<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/quick-content-that-makes-an-impact.html">Quick Content That Makes An Impact</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://killerinfographics.com">Killer Infographics</a>.</p>
";s:12:"atom_content";s:13300:"
		<div id="fws_5aba0ae472e04"  data-midnight="dark" data-bg-mobile-hidden="" class="wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_row standard_section   "  style="padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; "><div class="row-bg-wrap"><div class="inner-wrap"> <div class="row-bg    "  style="" data-color_overlay="" data-color_overlay_2="" data-gradient_direction="" data-overlay_strength="0.3" data-enable_gradient="false"></div></div> </div><div class="col span_12 dark left">
	<div  class="vc_col-sm-12 wpb_column column_container vc_column_container col no-extra-padding"  data-border-radius="none" data-shadow="none" data-border-animation="" data-border-animation-delay="" data-border-width="none" data-border-style="solid" data-border-color="" data-bg-cover="" data-padding-pos="all" data-has-bg-color="false" data-bg-color="" data-bg-opacity="1" data-hover-bg="" data-hover-bg-opacity="1" data-animation="" data-delay="0">
		<div class="vc_column-inner">
			<div class="wpb_wrapper">
				<div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="550" width="1200" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-header.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-header.jpg 1200w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-header-300x138.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-header-768x352.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-header-1024x469.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="visual content marketing" /></div></div><div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 25px;" class="divider"></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you?ve ever written a blog, posted a photo to Instagram, or even tweeted, then you?ve created microcontent, and it?s one of the most effective ways to reach an audience. Like its name implies, </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/numbers-2-unite-a-micro-content-series.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">microcontent is short or quick</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. But this small content can make a much bigger impression ? if done correctly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Making quick content is easy. But making quick content that?s good takes a well-planned strategy. Just because something is brief doesn?t mean it?s guaranteed to catch your readers? attentions.</span></p>
<p><b>What Exactly Is Microcontent?<br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Microcontent has been defined and redefined over the years. As our computers went from desktops to laptops to cell phones, microcontent evolved with it. Today, we like to think of microcontent as anything concise that can stand on its own. It?s not a new concept, but a changing one.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consider the headline. Newspaper headlines ? whether in a 16th-century flyer or on your news app of choice today ? communicate in a concise way. The good ones tell readers that you have more to offer them. In addition to the newspaper, that headline can live digitally on the paper?s website, its Twitter, its Facebook, and more.</span></p>
<p>And microcontent comes in many forms, including the following:</p>

		</div>
	</div>
<div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 25px;" class="divider"></div></div><div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="600" width="1200" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-1-copy.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-1-copy.jpg 1200w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-1-copy-300x150.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-1-copy-768x384.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-1-copy-1024x512.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="visual communication services" /></div></div><div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 25px;" class="divider"></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><b>Being Proactive and Reactive With Microcontent<br />
</b>There?s a good chance you already have some strong pieces for a <a href="http://killerinfographics.com/multimedia-and-visual-campaigns">microcontent campaign</a> and just haven?t realized it yet.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">An infographic, for example, is composed of several pieces that likely have substantial value on their own. Take them apart, share them where relevant, and see how your audience reacts. Maybe you?ll find these pieces ? </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/4-ways-to-stretch-your-infographic-content.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">whether clusters of data or captivating illustrations</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ? work as a series in microcontent. From there, you can create new content that wasn?t necessarily included on your infographic.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">And while standalone pieces of visual content are powerful in their own right, when united with a broader set of goals, the impact can be so much greater. Approaching a project proactively with a complete toolkit at hand for a </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/multimedia-and-visual-campaigns"><span style="font-weight: 400;">visual campaign</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> will allow you take your audience through a comprehensive journey of awareness, engagement, and results.</span></p>
<p><b>Small Content, but Big Results</b></p>

		</div>
	</div>
<div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 25px;" class="divider"></div></div><div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="615" width="1200" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-2-copy.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-2-copy.jpg 1200w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-2-copy-300x154.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-2-copy-768x394.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-2-copy-1024x525.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="attention spans on decline" /></div></div><div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 25px;" class="divider"></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A 2015 study on brain activity revealed </span><a class="" href="http://www.adweek.com/digital/john-stevens-guest-post-decreasing-attention-spans/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">attention spans are declining</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ? rapidly. In the year 2000, it was already fairly short at 12 seconds. But 15 years later, it had dipped to a measly 8 seconds. If you?re trying to reach an audience, you?d better do it fast because the numbers say they aren?t waiting around.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A major benefit of microcontent is that it?s consumable by nature. That short attention span shouldn?t be an issue here, as your audience can interpret the piece of microcontent before they move on. It?s not the entire meal. It?s just a bite, but ideally it?s enough to bring them in for more.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">That brevity should be appealing to the creator as well. While the time needed to create microcontent might vary, it?s typically resource-friendly. A tweet is at most 140 characters. An Instagram post is 1-10 photos (depending on your use of the album image feature). A GIF is a handful of frames.</span></p>
<p><b>Sticking to Best Practices for Microcontent<br />
</b>Microcontent, just like anything else, needs a strategy that follows best practices. Fortunately, the best practices for microcontent don?t vary much from their bigger brothers and sisters, but some aspects of the different formats can use some special attention.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you?re creating a static piece of visual content, consider what will resonate with your target audience. It?s important to remember that visual doesn?t mean just pictures. Provide information and a story. For example, if you have a longform piece on a large issue, a good approach for your microcontent is to introduce the problem, explain why it matters, and </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/4-content-keys-to-compelling-data-visualization.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">present a solution</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Maybe you?re trying an animated approach. On average, only 40% of viewers watch a </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/project/motion-graphic-the-history-of-vaccines"><span style="font-weight: 400;">motion graphic over 90 seconds</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to completion.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Your GIFs will be much shorter than this, but the lesson is the same: keep it short.</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>
<div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 25px;" class="divider"></div></div><div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="550" width="1200" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-3-copy.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-3-copy.jpg 1200w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-3-copy-300x138.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-3-copy-768x352.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Quick-Content-That-Makes-an-Impact-3-copy-1024x469.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="motion graphic statistics" /></div></div><div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 25px;" class="divider"></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p>And no matter what you?re making, it?s always important to stay on brand. This will allow you to create sincere, replicable content.</p>
<p><b>Think Ahead, but Think Fast<br />
</b>In 2013, the Baltimore Ravens won the Super Bowl, but Oreo ? yes, the cookie brand ? won it too. While companies were paying millions of dollars to run commercials, Oreo did it with a tweet. During the game, the power went out in the stadium. It was an unplanned, unpredictable event, and people took to the internet to talk about it, including <a class="" href="https://twitter.com/oreo/status/298246571718483968?lang=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Oreo</a>.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The people at Oreo didn?t know the power was going to go out. But its team knew it was one of the biggest events of the year, so </span><a class="" href="https://www.wired.com/2013/02/oreo-twitter-super-bowl/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">they were prepared to react</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to whatever did happen that day by having a 15-person social team at the ready. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">While the Super Bowl only comes once a year, the opportunities for microcontent come daily, and should be a core part of your content strategy.</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>

			</div> 
		</div>
	</div> 
</div></div>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/quick-content-that-makes-an-impact.html">Quick Content That Makes An Impact</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://killerinfographics.com">Killer Infographics</a>.</p>
";s:12:"link_replies";s:167:"http://killerinfographics.com/blog/quick-content-that-makes-an-impact.html#commentshttp://killerinfographics.com/blog/quick-content-that-makes-an-impact.html/feed/atom";}i:9;a:10:{s:6:"author";s:10:"
			
					";s:11:"author_name";s:13:"Abi Pollokoff";s:5:"title";s:43:"Motion Graphics and the Art of the Abstract";s:4:"link";s:68:"http://killerinfographics.com/blog/motion-graphics-art-abstract.html";s:2:"id";s:38:"http://killerinfographics.com/?p=14176";s:7:"updated";s:20:"2018-02-07T00:54:36Z";s:9:"published";s:20:"2017-12-07T17:00:54Z";s:7:"summary";s:256:"<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/motion-graphics-art-abstract.html">Motion Graphics and the Art of the Abstract</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://killerinfographics.com">Killer Infographics</a>.</p>
";s:12:"atom_content";s:13295:"
		<div id="fws_5aba0ae47b588"  data-midnight="dark" data-bg-mobile-hidden="" class="wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_row standard_section   "  style="padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; "><div class="row-bg-wrap"><div class="inner-wrap"> <div class="row-bg    "  style="" data-color_overlay="" data-color_overlay_2="" data-gradient_direction="" data-overlay_strength="0.3" data-enable_gradient="false"></div></div> </div><div class="col span_12 dark left">
	<div  class="vc_col-sm-12 wpb_column column_container vc_column_container col no-extra-padding"  data-border-radius="none" data-shadow="none" data-border-animation="" data-border-animation-delay="" data-border-width="none" data-border-style="solid" data-border-color="" data-bg-cover="" data-padding-pos="all" data-has-bg-color="false" data-bg-color="" data-bg-opacity="1" data-hover-bg="" data-hover-bg-opacity="1" data-animation="" data-delay="0">
		<div class="vc_column-inner">
			<div class="wpb_wrapper">
				<div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="2293" width="5001" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-01.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-01.jpg 5001w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-01-300x138.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-01-768x352.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-01-1024x470.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="motion graphic design" /></div></div><div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 40px;" class="divider"></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Motion graphics tell stories: stories of products, of studies, of whatever your business needs. The medium interweaves threads of visual and aural communication to </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/engaging-audience-video-content.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">connect with viewers</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> on numerous levels. And in telling these many-textured narratives, motion graphics rely on storytelling techniques to achieve their goals. One such technique is that of the comparison ? but while metaphor and simile in writing can help develop audience relationships, they can dilute the accuracy of technical information. Relying on the abstract (rather than the concrete) allows motion graphics to </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/measuring-the-roi-of-motion-graphics.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">double</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> their communication efforts via narrative, art direction, and animation.</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>
<div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 40px;" class="divider"></div></div><div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="1876" width="5001" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-02.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-02.jpg 5001w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-02-300x113.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-02-768x288.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-02-1024x384.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="animated explainer videos" /></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><b>Narrative Abstraction<br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Not all motion graphics have voiceover. Some rely on music or on-screen text to build momentum. However, when working with technical material, a voiceover makes room for boosted communication ? especially with a technical subject matter. Here?s why: the voiceover doubles your opportunity for communication.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When a voiceover describes a technical subject matter, you?ve freed up your screen to ?translate? that technical story into an abstract one. Without losing any accuracy, your viewer can hear the specifics while receiving a visual</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">comparison, giving them something to understand in associative terms. By balancing communication between visual and auditory comprehension, you?ve expanded your ability to communicate quickly, clearly, and effectively.</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>
<div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 40px;" class="divider"></div></div><div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="1876" width="5001" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-03.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-03.jpg 5001w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-03-300x113.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-03-768x288.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-03-1024x384.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="abstract motion graphics" /></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><b>Art Direction Abstraction<br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether or not your narrative takes an abstract approach, consider whether your motion graphic?s visuals should be abstract as well. Complex and technical content lends itself well to abstract visuals. When a shape represents a complicated idea, it relies on symbol rather than literal meaning to bring life to an idea, giving a viewer the chance to quickly understand the big picture rather than an element?s detail. If your subject matter is technical, there?s a chance that it might be patented or under development while your motion graphic is being produced. Abstract art gives you the opportunity to </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/4-video-marketing-trends-for-2017.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">communicate your primary ideas</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> without compromising the integrity of your product, process, or security.</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>
<div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 40px;" class="divider"></div></div><div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="1876" width="5001" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-04.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-04.jpg 5001w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-04-300x113.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-04-768x288.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-04-1024x384.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="animated stories" /></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><b>Animation Abstraction<br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once your art is finalized, you?ve thought through your narrative and what represents it for your viewers. One of the final pieces to the motion graphic puzzle ? the animation ? is another opportunity for some abstract support. No matter whether your narrative or visual direction have used abstract techniques, animation can convey tone and movement through non-realistic means. Abstract animation techniques include:</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  vc_custom_1510684372294" >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pulsing</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sliding</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Expanding</span></li>
</ul>

		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether or not your subject matter would deliver these movements in real life, each of these techniques can signal emphasis, hierarchy, or narrative development for the reader. And, abstract animation </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">can</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> be a budget-saver! Character animation or complicated movements can take time to create and align with music or voiceover, but subtle animations can keep your project scope in check while conveying specific meaning.</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>
<div class="divider-wrap"><div style="height: 40px;" class="divider"></div></div><div class="img-with-aniamtion-wrap " data-max-width="100%" data-border-radius="none"><div class="inner"><img data-shadow="none" data-shadow-direction="middle" class="img-with-animation " data-delay="0" height="1876" width="5001" data-animation="fade-in" src="http://killerinfographics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-05.jpg" srcset="http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-05.jpg 5001w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-05-300x113.jpg 300w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-05-768x288.jpg 768w, http://2fhd5y2itip42q28gh4cz5ln.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/KillerInternalBlog_MotionAbstraction_DES_09.22.17_v3-05-1024x384.jpg 1024w" sizes="100vw" alt="create motion graphics" /></div></div>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><b>A Concrete Conclusion<br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Abstract elements in narrative, art, and animation can build layers of meaning, simplify technical material, and develop audience relationships. Keep in mind, though: abstract terms </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">don?t</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> mean unclear ones. If you?re working with abstract elements, keep strong visual communication tenets in mind. </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/video-platform-rundown-vimeo-vs-youtube.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Each decision</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> should help you further clarity and key messaging for your viewers. With well-considered decisions and a touch of the abstract, your </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/blog/the-value-of-motion-graphics.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">motion graphic</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> can communicate clearly and effectively for any goal.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Have you used abstract elements in your motion graphics? </span><a href="http://killerinfographics.com/contact-us"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tell us</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> about it.</span></p>

		</div>
	</div>

			</div> 
		</div>
	</div> 
